%2C%20before%20you%20serve%20them%2C%20there%20shouldn't%20be%20outbreaks%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColorado%20resident%20Eric%20Stelly%20alleges%20in%20his%20lawsuit%20that%20he%20ate%20food%20from%20his%20local%20McDonald's%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Greeley%20on%20October%204%20and%20two%20days%20later%20fell%20ill%20with%20E.%20coli%20symptoms%2C%20which%20include%20bloody%20diarrhea%20and%20vomiting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20October%208%2C%20Stelly%20was%20hospitalized%20and%20he%20later%20tested%20positive%20for%20the%20E.%20coli%20O157%3AH7%20strain%20%E2%80%94%20the%20same%20E.%20coli%20strain%20federal%20health%20officials%20said%20was%20linked%20to%20the%20outbreak%20%E2%80%94%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20filed%20by%20Simon's%20firm%20along%20with%20the%20firm%20Meyers%20%26amp%3B%20Flowers%2C%20LLC%2C%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%2C%20which%20alleges%20negligence%20by%20McDonald's%2C%20says%20that%20health%20investigators%20confirmed%20Stelly%20was%20part%20of%20the%20E.%20coli%20outbreak%20linked%20to%20McDonalds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20McDonald's%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20by%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20Simon%20said%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-ecoli-outbreak-investigation-update-compared-chipotle-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcDonald's-related%20E.%20coli%20outbreak%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bwill%20be%20one%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20food%20poisoning%20outbreaks%20this%20year.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThrough%20this%20lawsuit%20and%20others%2C%20we%20will%20make%20sure%20that%20all%20of%20the%20victims%20are%20fully%20compensated%20for%20their%20losses%2C%20that%20their%20voices%20are%20heard%2C%20and%20that%20McDonald's%20and%20its%20suppliers%20permanently%20fix%20the%20health%20and%20safety%20violations%20that%20caused%20their%20food%20to%20become%20contaminated%20with%20E.%20coli%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimon%20%E2%80%94%20who%20also%20filed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboars-head-listeria-outbreak-deli-meat-death-holocaust-survivor-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrongful%20death%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20behalf%20of%20a%20Holocaust%20survivor's%20family%20against%20Boar's%20Head%20in%20connection%20to%20the%20recent%20deli%20meat%20listeria%20outbreak%20%E2%80%94%20told%20BI%20that%20he%20expects%20McDonald's%20to%20settle%20the%20anticipated%20onslaught%20of%20claims%20for%20millions%20of%20dollars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20gross%20negligence%20on%20McDonald's%20part%20not%20to%20try%20to%20resolve%20these%20cases%2C%26quot%3B%20Simon%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20were%20clearly%20mistakes%20made%20in%20the%20testing%20process%20%E2%80%94%20food%20that%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20safe%20was%20not%20safe.%20It%20was%20contaminated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%20said%20Tuesday%20that%20the%20E.%20coli%20outbreak%20has%20so%20far%20sickened%20at%20least%2049%20people%20across%2010%20states%20and%20resulted%20in%20one%20death.%20The%20outbreak%20was%20linked%20to%2010%20hospitalizations%2C%20with%20most%20of%20the%20illnesses%20occurring%20in%20Colorado%20and%20Nebraska%2C%20according%20to%20the%20CDC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20people%20impacted%20reported%20eating%20McDonald's%20Quarter%20Pounder%20hamburgers%20before%20becoming%20sick%2C%20the%20federal%20agency%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestigators%20are%20working%20to%20confirm%20which%20ingredient%20in%20the%20hamburgers%20is%20responsible%20for%20the%20contamination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcDonald's%20said%20it%20paused%20the%20distribution%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-ecoli-outbreak-investigation-update-compared-chipotle-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslivered%20onions%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%